==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farcical
<hw>Far"ci*cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to
farce; appropriated to farce; ludicrous; unnatural; unreal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They deny the characters to be <qex>farcical</qex>, because they
are actually in nature.</q> <rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Far"ci*cal*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-<wf>Far"ci*cal*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farcical</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Farcical
<hw>Far"ci*cal</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the disease
called farcy. See <er>Farcy</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farcilite</ent>⟦br⟧
